HEADWORD: Sivatherium
<hw>Siv`a*the"ri*um</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., from
E. <ets>Siva</ets> + Gr. <?/<?/<?/<?/ a beast, an animal.]</ety>
<fld>(Paleon.)</fld> <def>A genus of very large extinct ruminants found
in the Tertiary formation of India. The snout was prolonged in the form
of a proboscis. The male had four horns, the posterior pair being large
and branched. It was allied to the antelopes, but very much larger than
any existing species.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Siver</ent>⟦br⟧
